SHARING PAID OPPORTUNITY 

I‚Äôm Jude, casting with Liz Lewis Casting Partners, and I wanted to share a current project we‚Äôre working on for Metamucil.

For this particular project, we are actually looking for real Metamucil users, ages 45‚Äì60, with no professional acting or performing experience. While we know this community is full of talented actors, we wanted to share here in case you might know friends, family members, or people in your network who could be a great fit.

It‚Äôs a nationwide search. The shoot location is still being finalized and may be Austin, or possibly Mexico or Canada. If travel is required, production will cover all travel and accommodations.

Compensation is $500 per shoot day, plus $3,400 for 1-year usage, all media.

**Participants cannot have any professional performing experience, including paid acting, dancing, or singing work (union or non-union). **

To submit please click on this link [Metamucil Form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSffQ4Zl_-5Evj8FE5NNi9aTaYuc-htYG1gLG25xmTIcI_CM4g/viewform?usp=header)

If this sounds like you or someone you know, feel free to reach out or share!

Vom Filmset ins echte Leben, Sergio Klee und Christian Wei√üe sprechen √ºber Sicherheit, Wahrnehmung und Setkultur 

Wenn Ver√§nderung den Blick sch√§rft 

In diesem Teil erz√§hlt Sergio Klee, wie pers√∂nliche Entwicklung die eigene Pr√§senz am Set ver√§ndert. Er beschreibt, wie innere Anspannung weicht, wenn man versteht, woher Nervosit√§t wirklich kommt. Durch die Reflexion seines eigenen Weges zeigt er, wie Selbstkritik lauter sein kann als jedes Lob und weshalb Sicherheit erst entsteht, wenn man sich selbst erkennt statt sich zu verstecken. 

Wahrnehmung, Ego und die Kunst, nichts pers√∂nlich zu nehmen 

Sergio schildert eine Situation, in der er an einem Set offen √§u√üerte, wo er sich wohlf√ºhlt, und pl√∂tzlich in kritische Blicke lief. Er erkl√§rt, wie schnell Menschen neutrale Aussagen bewerten und warum das Ego immer eine Wertung sucht, auch wenn keine da ist. 

Von Atmosph√§re, Respekt und Kleinigkeiten mit grosser Wirkung 

Die Episode zeigt, wie unterschiedlich Drehtage wirken k√∂nnen. Sergio vergleicht Setkulturen, Catering, Umgangsformen und kleine Gesten, die den Unterschied zwischen distanziert und famili√§r ausmachen. Seine Erfahrungen bei Formaten wie K√∂ln 50667, Alles was z√§hlt, Barbara Salesch und Ulrich Wetzel machen deutlich, wie stark Wertsch√§tzung das eigene Gef√ºhl von Zugeh√∂rigkeit pr√§gt und warum sich manche Orte sofort richtig anf√ºhlen. 

Reinwachsen in Abl√§ufe und R√§ume, bis die Kamera l√§uft 

Sergio beschreibt, wie man bei jedem neuen Projekt zuerst fremd wirkt, dann Orientierung findet und schlie√ülich ankommt. Vom ersten Guten Tag im B√ºro √ºber Kost√ºm und Maske bis zur laufenden Kamera zeigt er, wie viel Sicherheit in Wiederholung und Vorbereitung steckt. Das Gespr√§ch √∂ffnet einen seltenen Einblick in die leisen Momente vor dem Take, in denen man begreift, dass man dazugeh√∂rt. 

Zu mir, Christian Wei√üe 

Ich bin Christian Wei√üe, Medienunternehmer, Content Creator und Inhaber der Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion aus K√∂ln. Ich entwickle Bewegtbildformate, erz√§hle Geschichten f√ºr Unternehmen, Organisationen und Pers√∂nlichkeiten und kenne als Darsteller beide Seiten der Kamera. 

Abonniere den Kanal, like das Video, teile deine Gedanken in den Kommentaren und besuche mind_body_coach_ auf Instagram f√ºr weitere Impulse von Sergio Klee. 

Christian Wei√üe / Karrideo Imagefilm-Produktion / Karrideo Imagefilm-Produktion - Zuschauer, Auftraggeber, Partner

If you wish to audition please fill out the google form and send in your tape using the sides. Everything needed to do this will be listed on our linktree.

Neila (30s) Woman Any Ethnicity:  Emotionally withdrawn, traumatised by her partner‚Äôs death, which she accidentally caused.  Stiff and guarded, Neila carries a deep shame and self-contempt‚Ä¶ but underneath that, a tenderness, vulnerability, and a desire for acceptance and affection.

Casey (30s) Any Gender, Any Ethnicity : Kind and sensitive, nervous and jittery. Possesses the power of psychometry: the ability to learn people or objects‚Äô history by touch. Filled with shame about this potentially invasive trait, which has always kept them from truly connecting with others. Despite their constant caution, they maintains a positive attitude.

Server (20s) Any Gender, Any Ethnicity : New to the job a little jittery, but kind soul.

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì STARFARM 

We‚Äôre casting fun, stylish young women (15‚Äì25) for an unscripted eco-reality series!

AI is taking over the world. Replacing jobs, replacing people, reforming industries. They are humanity's greatest creation yet our ultimate competition. Now, an unscripted eco-reality series featuring 10 young women, learning to live on a completely remote and self-sustainable farm - across the dirt road, lies another self-sustained farm; run by AI. Will they survive or thrive? Will they change the future for the next generation of girls, by proving something woman-powered can be more fruitful than something AI-powered?

Hey zusammen üëã

ich teile das hier, weil ich wei√ü, wie hart unser Weg manchmal ist. Viele von uns geben alles, spielen gut und werden trotzdem nicht wirklich gesehen. Vielleicht hilft Dir das hier ein St√ºck weiter.

Ich habe einen kostenlosen 7 Tage E Mail Kurs erstellt. Jeden Tag bekommst Du eine kleine √úbung, die Dir sofort etwas bringt und die Du ganz entspannt in Deinen Alltag einbauen kannst. Enthalten sind auch hilfreiche Tipps zu Castern, Agenturen und vielem, was uns Schauspielerinnen und Schauspieler wirklich besch√§ftigt.

Nach den 7 Tagen bekommst Du ein Jahr lang einmal pro Woche kurze Impulse zu Schauspiel, Pr√§senz, Mindset und auch Sichtbarkeit aus meiner eigenen Arbeit vor und hinter der Kamera.

Kurz zu mir, damit Du wei√üt, wer das hier teilt:

Ich bin Roberto aus M√ºnchen

üé≠ international mehrfach ausgezeichnet als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent
üìΩÔ∏è CEO der Lucky Eagle Production GmbH
üèÜ Jurymitglied beim FilmHaus Berlin
üåç arbeite seit Jahren in internationalen Film und Serienprojekten

Ich arbeite unglaublich gern mit Schauspielerinnen und Schauspielern und teile das Wissen, das mir selbst auf meinem Weg wirklich geholfen hat.

Wenn Du magst, findest Du hier den Kurs und ein Video, in dem ein paar meiner Mentees erz√§hlen, wie sie meine Arbeit erlebt haben:

üëâ kurs.nextstagecoaching.de

Vielleicht hilft es Dir oder jemandem aus Deinem Umfeld. Gib es gerne weiter, wenn es jemand brauchen kann ‚ò∫Ô∏è

Und denk immer daran
Du bist genug. Genau jetzt. ü´∂

Roberto

items.text:
Do you have experience working with children and young people aged 6-18? Do you have a passion for musical theatre and dancing, singing and acting? Are you looking for an opportunity to combine your skills and interests to develop young people in a fun and professional setting? Then PQA Haywards Heath is just the place for you!

Due to the success of our growing academy, The Pauline Quirke Academy of Performing Arts (PQA), a leading provider of weekend performing arts training, is currently recruiting MUSICAL THEATRE TEACHER for their Academy in Haywards Heath on Saturday mornings and/or afternoons.

We are searching for fun, engaging and passionate individuals looking to bring lots of exciting and innovative ideas to our Musical Theatre module. If you are passionate about learning, the performing arts and making a positive impact on the lives of young people, we would be delighted to hear from you!

PQA follows safer recruiting. An enhanced DBS on the update service will be required and can be arranged. Applicants must be 18+.

To apply please email your CV with a cover letter explaining why you would be the ideal candidate for this role. Please send these direct to Principal Florence on florence.tingley@pqacademy.com.

We look forward to hearing from you!

items.text:
Another incredible piece of feedback for The Trinity Acting Method.
Stephen has already powered through to Chapter Five and his words genuinely mean the world:

‚ÄúThe breakdown and how to approach scripts, behavioural choices etc. is great and straight to the point‚Ä¶ I get so tired of reading books that go round the houses to get to a small nugget of information. So far I find what I‚Äôve read a direct path to information. Well done.‚Äù

This is exactly why I wrote the book ‚Äî clear, actionable, modern screen-acting guidance with no wasted words.
If you haven‚Äôt grabbed your copy yet, you can get it here:

üëâ Amazon link: https://amzn.to/3XIQNj4

Thank you Stephen ‚Äî and thank you to everyone supporting this journey. üôå

‚∏ª

#TheTrinityActingMethod #MattZina #ScreenActing #ActingBooks #ActorTraining
#ActingTips #ActingCoach #UKActors #AmazonAuthor #ActingJourney #ActingCommunity #ActorsLife

üö® Casting announcement ‚Äì feature film üö®
Sunny Runny Productions in collaboration with Going Nowhere Productions

We‚Äôre casting two roles for our upcoming feature film No Gentle Goodnight, shooting early 2026 in Runcorn, Cheshire.

This is a low-budget production following Equity low-budget guidelines for professional actors, with payment via a profit share contract. Local expenses will be covered and catering provided on shoot days. IMDB credit included. Please note that accommodation is not available for this project.

Roles

Male ‚Äì Age 35‚Äì50
Father of the protagonist (voiceover only, for a flashback scene)

Female ‚Äì Age 25‚Äì40
Mother of young David (appears in a flashback scene)

Both roles need authenticity and heart, but no previous acting experience is necessary, especially for people local to the area. Anyone is welcome to apply.

Auditions will take place in early January

Send Headshots, Spotlight/showreel links and CV or just a photo and a message saying why you would like the part.

Email subject: NGG Casting
Email: casting@sunnyrunnyproductions.com

About the project

-Festival-bound, character-driven indie film

-Proof-of-concept trailer already generating buzz

-Supported by a talented cast, crew and growing audience

Website: www.sunnyrunnyproductions.com

Instagram: @sunnyrunnyproductions
Twitter/X: @sunnyrunny2025 
TikTok: @sunnyrunnyproductions

Come and be part of a professional, welcoming production creating bold northern storytelling.

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúTALE OF TWO‚Äù (SHORT FILM) 

Hey all. I‚Äôm still looking for an older gentlemen for the role of Michael in my upcoming short. 45+ & white presenting. 

Logline:
‚ÄúTale of Two‚Äù is a portrait short film about women‚Äôs strength, focusing on our shared experiences rather than our differences. Through small, intimate scenes, we witness key moments in the lives of two women as they navigate hardship, love, and resilience in parallel journeys.

Production Details:

‚Ä¢ Location: Downtown Vancouver

‚Ä¢ Shoot Dates: 1-3 days ‚Äì end of January

‚Ä¢ Format: MOS (no sync sound) - performances will rely heavily on expressive, facial acting

‚Ä¢ Compensation: Volunteer basis with great meals, greater company, and IMDb credit.

To Submit:
Please send your headshot and CV/demo reel to taleoftwofilm@gmail.com.
Include a slate with your name, age, height, and any unavailable dates.
Submission Deadline: December 6th 4 pm

the wait is over! we are now accepting submissions for our summer production of ‚ÄúBe More Chill!‚Äù

for full details, visit the link in our bio.

Simone Nathalia - Director/Choreographer
Taylor McKee - Music Director
Madison Raybould - Choreographer
Morgan Da Silva-Rolph - Stage Manager

Music and Lyrics by Joe Iconis
Book by Joe Tracz
Based on the Novel by Ned Vizzini

audition dates
in-person: December 20th & 21st, 2025
callbacks: January 3rd, 2026
self-tapes: submissions due on Dec. 19th

audition venue:
Carousel Theatre for Young People, 1411 Cartwright St, Granville Island

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

what to prepare:
1. 2 contrasting musical theatre songs, (you may only be asked to sing one, but please have both ready).

2. a 1-2 minute contemporary, comedic monologue - this must be memorized.

how to apply:
please email your headshot and resume to theatre@xoxotv.ca to be scheduled with an audition time, or to request a self-tape submission.

character breakdowns can be found in our ‚Äúaudition package‚Äù link in bio.

production dates:
July 15th - 18th, 2026

production venue:
Firehall Arts Centre, 280 E Cordova St, Vancouver

notes:
rehearsals will begin April 30th, 2026
Saturdays 10:00am to 6:00pm
Tuesdays & Thursdays 6:00pm to 10:00pm

contact info@xoxotv.ca or DM us with any questions!

best of luck to all performers - we‚Äôll see you at auditions! üòÅüíÑüêæ

www.concordtheatricals.com
The world premiere production of Be More Chill was commissioned and originally produced by Two River Theater Company in Red Bank, NJ
John Dias, Artistic Director / Michael Hurst, Managing Director
This work was supported by a Theatre Commissioning and Production Initiative grant from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation
Orchestrations and Arrangements by Charlie Rosen

CASTING CALL ‚Äî Vancouver, BC (Union/Non-Union ‚Ä¢ Volunteer)

Project: BOYISH ‚Äî 4th Year Capilano University Short Film

Director: Vlada Hayvoronska

Filming Dates: Feb 6‚Äì8, 2026

We‚Äôre casting MIA and SKIPPER, two key supporting roles in a gritty, character-driven coming-of-age short about the messy shift from boyhood to adulthood.

MIA (supporting)

Female, 16‚Äì18 age-presenting (actor must be 18+)

Luka‚Äôs older sister. Loud, messy, protective, insecure underneath. Pretends she‚Äôs tough but she‚Äôs still figuring life out.

SKIPPER (supporting)Male, 25‚Äì35

A not-so-charming burnout. Lives off beer, validation, and vibes. Thinks he‚Äôs the ‚Äúwise older guy,‚Äù but he‚Äôs actually deeply stuck.

TO SUBMIT:

Email boyish2026@gmail.com

 with:

‚Ä¢ headshot

‚Ä¢ demo reel / clips

‚Ä¢ subject line: BOYISH ‚Äì MIA or BOYISH ‚Äì SKIPPER

Deadline: Dec 14th, 2025 ‚Äî 11:59 PM

Notes:

‚Ä¢ Union & non-union performers welcome

‚Ä¢ Volunteer project (student short; meals + credits provided)

‚Ä¢ Must be 18+

‚Ä¢ Diversity encouraged ‚Äî all backgrounds welcome

items.text:
Hi there

Can anyone recommend someone who can create (and script) a showreel please. 

For my 20 year old daughter. Trying very hard to carve her way into an acting career. Is registered with some extra agencies and has had some decent shoots but nothing consistent.

Also she can't get a spotlight account as she hasn't got credits hence the showreel request :) 

Anyone in Hertfordshire or NW London would be amazing. 

Also if anyone can recommend any other agencies not Rachels People - filled out the application form. Didn't even get a response. Tried emailing and filling out the online enquiry form a few times, still no response (it's hard enough as it is - a reply would have been nice but never mind). 

Any leads would be gratefully received (esp the showreel one)

Thanks

Worn down and trapped in denial. Loves her children but lacks the strength to protect them.

Jay (Playing age 18 - 23)

Tough, wiry, and street-smart but emotionally scarred. Trying to go straight yet haunted by anger and guilt. Deeply protective of Lucy. Needs quiet intensity and physical realism.

Tom (40 - 50s)

Manipulative, controlling stepfather. Charismatic on the surface, violent underneath. A coward masked as a bully. 

The synopsis for the film is

Breathing Still is a raw social-realist short film about Jay, a 19-year-old just out of prison, who returns home to protect his younger sister Lucy from their abusive stepfather Tom. As Jay struggles to stay out of trouble, old loyalties and buried rage threaten to drag him back into violence. When Tom‚Äôs cruelty turns physical, Jay is forced to choose between freedom and doing what‚Äôs right.

If interested please email me at jake.jakej@outlook.com or message me on 07507977991

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

**Casting Call for a 20-min short**

Hi everyone! We‚Äôre looking for non-union actors who are based on Vancouver, BC. We're thrilled to have new blood in our team! 

**Production Information: **

-Location: Vancouver, BC

-Shoot Dates: Jan 3rd-4th.

-Genre:Drama, Thriller

-Non-Union/Volunteer

-Crafty+IMDb credit provided 

**Roles: **

**Officer Shaw Male 28-50**

A true believer in justice and law enforcement. He doesn‚Äôt believe mentalism is anything more than cheap party tricks, but he finds Chaz and his shtick entertaining, so he allows Chaz to perform for him and explain himself. With every word Chaz says in his defence, Officer Shaw starts to see through Chaz‚Äôs persona and eventually confronts him about the moral, ethical and legal complications his profession entails. The conversation reaches a boiling point when Chaz attempts to read Officer Shaw‚Äôs mind by repeating the last words spoken to Shaw from his missing daughter.

**Mark Male 28-50**

A bitter, cynical man whose sole goal is to prove that Chaz and everything he stands for is a complete pile of crap. He questions everything, every small movement, every word Chaz says, he does not let anything slip. He is the worst participant a magician could possibly ask for. He believes that Chaz is exploiting people, lying to them about magical abilities in order to profit from manipulating the public‚Äôs belief. Nothing Chaz says or does can change his mind and he will stop at nothing to embarrass Chaz live on air and prove that Chaz is a complete fraud.

**Kayla Female 18-30**

Mark‚Äôs na√Øve podcast co-host. She is fascinated with the idea and concept of mentalism and thinks Chaz‚Äôs persona is incredibly exciting. She represents the average person obsessed with magic and mentalism. She loves tricks being performed on her and believes it‚Äôs all harmless

fun. She doesn‚Äôt see anything wrong with what Chaz is doing and truly believes he can read her mind. She tries to keep the order as Mark and Chaz scream at each other, simply wanting to have a fun time and create an entertaining show for her audience.

**To submit:**

Please submit headshot and demo reel to **theartofreadingminds.short@gmail.com** and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Mohamed Redha Zertal, Liverpool-based with a strong on-camera presence and real performance experience. 
I‚Äôm looking to collaborate on short films, drama pieces, and character-led projects across Liverpool, Manchester, and Salford.

What I bring:
‚Ä¢ Strong screen presence
‚Ä¢ Stand-up comedy experience (Hot Water Comedy Club)
‚Ä¢ Confident delivery + natural timing
‚Ä¢ Multilingual: Arabic, French, English
‚Ä¢ Athletic look ‚Äî ideal for police, detective, action, villain, father, security, or emotional drama roles
‚Ä¢ Reliable, disciplined, takes direction well
‚Ä¢ Comfortable with emotional scenes and dialogue-heavy roles

Availability:
‚Ä¢ Immediate
‚Ä¢ Flexible for rehearsals & shoot days
‚Ä¢ Same-day self-tapes

I can provide:
‚Ä¢ Professional headshots
‚Ä¢ 20‚Äì30 sec intro/showreel clip
‚Ä¢ Self-tape for any role
‚Ä¢ Full acting CV

If you need someone who shows up prepared, delivers, and treats your film seriously, feel free to message me.

Looking forward to working with talented filmmakers.
‚Äì Redha üé¨

Hello everyone,

I am currently casting for my student short film.

The roles I am casting for are 

Mum (Late 30s‚ÄìEarly 40s)

Worn down and trapped in denial. Loves her children but lacks the strength to protect them.

Jay (Playing age 18 - 23)

Tough, wiry, and street-smart but emotionally scarred. Trying to go straight yet haunted by anger and guilt. Deeply protective of Lucy. Needs quiet intensity and physical realism.

Tom (40 - 50s)

Manipulative, controlling stepfather. Charismatic on the surface, violent underneath. A coward masked as a bully. 

The synopsis for the film is

Breathing Still is a raw social-realist short film about Jay, a 19-year-old just out of prison, who returns home to protect his younger sister Lucy from their abusive stepfather Tom. As Jay struggles to stay out of trouble, old loyalties and buried rage threaten to drag him back into violence. When Tom‚Äôs cruelty turns physical, Jay is forced to choose between freedom and doing what‚Äôs right.

Production is taking place in Stoke-On-Trent, Production dates are 13th and 14th of December.

If interested please email me at jake.jakej@outlook.com or message me on 07507977991

‚ÄúSardines‚Äù follows five sardines as they bicker over life's meaning and their purpose in the world.

Self tapes are due by 31st December and the cast will be contacted by the new year.

Please note: this is a 20 min play and will be part of a three play evening. A profit share will be paid.

MARCEL (Hovedrolle)

Spillealder: 20-28

DEN FREMMEDE (B√¶rende bi-rolle)

OM FILMEN:

Frida og Marcel er begge midt i tyverne og er begge p√• hver sin m√•de g√•et i st√• i tilv√¶relsen. Frida f√∏ler, at hun sidder fast i sit ellers billedsk√∏nne og perfekte parforhold, og Marcel er lige blevet dumpet af pigen, han troede var sit livs k√¶rlighed.

I to parallelle handlingsforl√∏b kaster de sig ud i to vidt forskellige fors√∏g p√• at genfinde gnisten i den gr√• tilv√¶relse, p√• to forskellige dates, i to forskellige lejligheder p√• hver sin side af en opgang.

Vi er st√∏ttet af Aarhus Filmv√¶rksted, men er stadig en lavbudget-produktion drevet af passionerede frivillige. Projektet er derfor ikke l√∏nnet, men produktionen d√¶kker transport, samt m√•ltider og forfriskninger p√• set.

üìß Send en mail til [visitkortfilm@gmail.com](mailto:visitkortfilm@gmail.com) med titlen ‚ÄúCasting‚Äù efterfulgt af dit navn.

New dates added - Dec 8-19 in Las Vegas. To book go to https://rebrand.ly/freehdsht

FREE HEADSHOT and 1-HOUR SESSION ‚Äì East Summerlin, Las Vegas

Address sent automatically after booking

Hi! I‚Äôm Steve Fogarty, a Las Vegas headshot specialist and owner of EXPO TRAFFIC, where we run large-scale headshot activations for major trade shows (600-700 people over 2.5 days).

I‚Äôm currently testing new lighting setups and posing flows for upcoming conventions, and I‚Äôm looking for real people to sit for practice sessions in a more relaxed environment. In return for your time, you get a full headshot session and one professional, retouched headshot for free.

**What You Get**
* A 60‚Äì75 minute headshot session
* Multiple looks + lighting setups
* A private online gallery
* One edited, retouched image included
* Additional images optional (zero pressure)

**Examples of my retouching**

[https://rebrand.ly/retouching](https://rebrand.ly/retouching)

Why There‚Äôs a $20 Fee

It‚Äôs not a sales charge. It‚Äôs a **non-refundable security deposit and show-up guarantee** that ensures the schedule stays reliable for both of us. The $20 simply confirms your commitment to attend ‚Äî and your favorite image is still included for free.

How You Get Your Image

After the session:
* We will review your images, and you'll tell me which ones are your favorites that you do not want deleted.
* I will edit and retouch your favorites, then upload them to your private gallery.
* You can download your favorite image using a coupon code (provided).
* You‚Äôre welcome to purchase extras, but it‚Äôs totally optional.

What to Expect / How to Prepare
* Arrive camera-ready (mirror + restroom available)
* Plan for 3‚Äì4 different looks
* Avoid pure white tops if possible
* Relax ‚Äî I‚Äôll guide you through every pose and expression

Safety + Professionalism
* All public areas are video security-monitored for your comfort and safety
* Private areas (bathrooms, changing areas) are never recorded
* References available by request

You can preview my work here:

[https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots](https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots)

**Location**

**East Summerlin near Rainbow & Alta**

**Exact address provided after booking.**

**Looking forward to creating something great together!**

**‚Äì Steve Fogarty**

**Owner ‚Äì STEVEN JOSEPH PHOTOGRAPHY | EXPO TRAFFIC HEADSHOTS**

I‚Äôm currently testing new lighting setups and posing flows for upcoming conventions, and I‚Äôm looking for real people to sit for practice sessions in a more relaxed environment. In return for your time, you get a full headshot session and one professional, retouched headshot for free.

**What You Get**
* A 60‚Äì75 minute headshot session
* Multiple looks + lighting setups
* A private online gallery
* One edited, retouched image included
* Additional images optional (zero pressure)

**Examples of my retouching**

[https://rebrand.ly/retouching](https://rebrand.ly/retouching)

Why There‚Äôs a $20 Fee

It‚Äôs not a sales charge. It‚Äôs a **non-refundable security deposit and show-up guarantee** that ensures the schedule stays reliable for both of us. The $20 simply confirms your commitment to attend ‚Äî and your favorite image is still included for free.

How You Get Your Image

After the session:
* We will review your images, and you'll tell me which ones are your favorites that you do not want deleted.
* I will edit and retouch your favorites, then upload them to your private gallery.
* You can download your favorite image using a coupon code (provided).
* You‚Äôre welcome to purchase extras, but it‚Äôs totally optional.

What to Expect / How to Prepare
* Arrive camera-ready (mirror + restroom available)
* Plan for 3‚Äì4 different looks
* Avoid pure white tops if possible
* Relax ‚Äî I‚Äôll guide you through every pose and expression

Safety + Professionalism
* All public areas are video security-monitored for your comfort and safety
* Private areas (bathrooms, changing areas) are never recorded
* References available by request

You can preview my work here:

[https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots](https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots)

**Location**

**East Summerlin near Rainbow & Alta**

**Exact address provided after booking.**

**Looking forward to creating something great together!**

**‚Äì Steve Fogarty**

**Owner ‚Äì STEVEN JOSEPH PHOTOGRAPHY | EXPO TRAFFIC HEADSHOTS**

items.text:
Just wondering where do people usually find acting extras jobs? 
I'm wanting to get into the industry and being an extra seems the best way but im not sure actually how to get started. 
Would love some advice üòäüòä

topComments.text: An actor/actress and an extra are two totally different jobs.

If you are interested in acting rather than SA work,  I recommend getting hold of a copy of Actors and Performers Yearbook which gives a good brief overview of the profession and helps to explain how industry casting works and who does what.  

There is very rarely a "progression" from SA work to acting work as actors and extras are engaged differently.

If you do want extra/SA work then joining extras agencies is the way to go.  

There's an SA Facebook group called Heavy Pencil for SAs which you may find interesting.  

Casting Collective (and a number of other agencies) have some fairly comprehensive information on their websites about extra work.

attachments.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'StuckUndertheSameSkim StuckUnd Stuck Under the Same Skin Sophiadarlingcasting.com com or Sophiadaring.casting@gmail.com ng.casting @gmail.com Savannah,GA GA April 17-19 & pril17-19&24-26 24-26'

May be an image of text that says 'GARY LEAD 28-35years 28- 28-35 years old Male A poet from inside and office worker for the people outside, whose mental and emotional exhaustion have aged him beyond his years; although Gary is chronologically young, his demeanor, thinking, and overall presence project the weariness of someone much older. The actor needs to be able to show Gary's shift from being closed off and stuck in his routine to someone who feels alive again. The change should come through subtle choices, the way he carries himself, his energy, even small shifts in expression, rather than big dramatic moments.'
May be an image of text

They care for their patience and keeps an open mind for anyone who comes through those doors. Receptionist: 20s-Mid 40S- The receptionist for MindSpace. They keep an open mind and pleasant smile on for anyone who comes through those doors. Teen(s) 18+ to play teens- Some teens who play soccer in in their free time.'
